-Now, take my case.

728
00:37:23,533 --> 00:37:25,410
They hung me up here
five years ago.

729
00:37:25,451 --> 00:37:27,579
Every night they take me down
for 20 minutes

730
00:37:27,620 --> 00:37:28,705
then they hang me up again.

731
00:37:28,747 --> 00:37:30,623
Which I regard as very fair

732
00:37:30,665 --> 00:37:32,250
in view of what I've done.

733
00:37:32,291 --> 00:37:36,880
And if nothing else, it's taught
me to respect the Romans

734
00:37:36,922 --> 00:37:40,550
and it's taught me that you'll
never get anywhere in this life

735
00:37:40,592 --> 00:37:43,595
unless you are prepared to do
a fair day's work

736
00:37:43,636 --> 00:37:46,305
-for a fair day's--
-Oh, shut up!

737
00:37:49,267 --> 00:37:51,603
-Pilate wants to see you!
-Me?

738
00:37:51,644 --> 00:37:53,021
Come on!

739
00:37:53,063 --> 00:37:54,856
[Brian] Pilate?
What does he want to see me for?

740
00:37:54,898 --> 00:37:57,275
I think he wants to know which
way you want to be crucified.

741
00:37:57,316 --> 00:37:59,861
Oh! [exaggerated laugh]

742
00:37:59,903 --> 00:38:02,197
Nice one, centurion.
Like it, like it.

743
00:38:02,239 --> 00:38:05,075
-Shut up!
-Right. Right.

744
00:38:06,201 --> 00:38:08,120
Terrific race, the Romans.

745
00:38:08,161 --> 00:38:10,080
Terrific.

746
00:38:10,122 --> 00:38:13,541
[fanfare plays]

747
00:38:20,799 --> 00:38:22,259
Looks like a nice living area.

748
00:38:22,300 --> 00:38:25,553
-[disappointed] Oh.
-[footsteps approaching]

749
00:38:27,430 --> 00:38:29,224
-Hail Caesar.
-Hail.

750
00:38:29,266 --> 00:38:30,391
Only one survivor, sir.

751
00:38:30,433 --> 00:38:33,394
Ah. Throw him
to the floor.

752
00:38:33,436 --> 00:38:36,397
-What, sir?
-Throw him to the floor.

753
00:38:36,439 --> 00:38:37,816
Oh.

754
00:38:38,900 --> 00:38:40,026
[groans]

755
00:38:40,068 --> 00:38:41,236
Humph.

756
00:38:41,278 --> 00:38:44,739
Now, what is
your name, Jew?

757
00:38:44,781 --> 00:38:47,742
-Brian, sir.
-[speech impediment] Brian, eh?

758
00:38:47,784 --> 00:38:49,494
No, no, Brian.

759
00:38:49,535 --> 00:38:51,913
-Ow!
-[Pilate chuckles]

760
00:38:51,955 --> 00:38:55,125
The little rascal has spirit.

761
00:38:55,167 --> 00:38:57,294
-Has what, sir?
-Spirit.

762
00:38:57,335 --> 00:38:59,420
Yes, he did, sir.

763
00:38:59,462 --> 00:39:01,464
No, no, spirit.

764
00:39:01,506 --> 00:39:04,342
Bravado,
a touch of derring-do.

765
00:39:04,383 --> 00:39:07,012
Oh, uh, about 11, sir.

766
00:39:09,139 --> 00:39:11,390
So...

767
00:39:11,432 --> 00:39:14,060
-You dare to raid us?
-To what, sir?

768
00:39:14,102 --> 00:39:16,980
Strike him, centurion,
very roughly.

769
00:39:17,022 --> 00:39:19,440
-Ahh!
-Oh, and, uh...

770
00:39:19,482 --> 00:39:21,026
throw him to the floor, sir?

771
00:39:21,067 --> 00:39:23,028
-What?
-Throw him to the floor again,
sir?

772
00:39:23,069 --> 00:39:25,530
Oh, yes.
Throw him to the floor, please.

773
00:39:26,698 --> 00:39:27,824
Ahh!

774
00:39:27,866 --> 00:39:31,369
Now, Jewish
rapscallion...

775
00:39:31,410 --> 00:39:33,579
I'm not Jewish,
I'm a Roman.

776
00:39:33,621 --> 00:39:36,499
-A Roman?
-No, no, Roman.

777
00:39:36,541 --> 00:39:38,417
Ahh!

778
00:39:38,459 --> 00:39:39,919
So...

779
00:39:39,961 --> 00:39:42,130
your father
was a Roman?

780
00:39:42,172 --> 00:39:43,589
Who was he?

781
00:39:43,631 --> 00:39:47,719
He was a centurion
in the Jerusalem garrison, sir.

782
00:39:47,760 --> 00:39:49,179
Really?

783
00:39:49,221 --> 00:39:52,431
-What was his name?
-Naughtius Maximus.

784
00:39:52,473 --> 00:39:54,392
[laughs heartily]

785
00:39:56,644 --> 00:39:59,856
Centurion, do you have anyone
of that name in the garrison?

786
00:40:00,982 --> 00:40:02,984
Well, no, sir.

787
00:40:03,026 --> 00:40:06,154
Well, you sound very sure.
Have you checked?

788
00:40:06,196 --> 00:40:07,572
Well, no, sir, um...

789
00:40:07,613 --> 00:40:10,200
I think it's a joke, sir.

790
00:40:10,242 --> 00:40:12,035
Like "Sillius Soddus"

791
00:40:12,077 --> 00:40:13,995
or "Biggus Dickus," sir.

792
00:40:14,037 --> 00:40:15,580
[men stifle laughter]

793
00:40:15,621 --> 00:40:19,625
What's so funny
about Biggus Dickus?

794
00:40:20,793 --> 00:40:24,047
Well, it's a joke name, sir.

795
00:40:24,089 --> 00:40:27,133
I have a very great friend
in Rome called Biggus Dickus.

796
00:40:27,175 --> 00:40:28,426
[guard stifles laugh]

797
00:40:30,095 --> 00:40:32,847
Silence!
What is all this insolence?

798
00:40:32,889 --> 00:40:36,601
You will find yourself in
gladiator school very quickly

799
00:40:36,642 --> 00:40:38,519
with rotten behavior like that.

800
00:40:38,561 --> 00:40:40,188
Can I go now, sir?

801
00:40:40,230 --> 00:40:42,523
Ahh!

802
00:40:42,565 --> 00:40:44,483
Wait till Biggus Dickus
hears of this.

803
00:40:44,525 --> 00:40:46,361
-[stifles laugh]
-Right!

804
00:40:46,403 --> 00:40:48,529
-Take him away!
-Oh, sir, he--

805
00:40:48,571 --> 00:40:51,783
No, no, I want him fighting
rabid wild animals
within a week!

806
00:40:51,824 --> 00:40:53,492
Yes, sir. Come on, you.

807
00:40:53,534 --> 00:40:57,580
[laughing]

808
00:40:57,622 --> 00:41:03,669
I will not have my friends
ridiculed by the common
soldiery!

809
00:41:05,171 --> 00:41:08,341
Anybody else
feel like a little...

810
00:41:08,383 --> 00:41:09,717
giggle

811
00:41:09,759 --> 00:41:13,846
when I mention my friend,

812
00:41:13,888 --> 00:41:15,807
Biggus

813
00:41:17,058 --> 00:41:19,436
-Dickus?
-[soldiers snicker]

814
00:41:22,314 --> 00:41:23,982
And what about you?

815
00:41:24,023 --> 00:41:27,068
Do you find it... risible

816
00:41:29,362 --> 00:41:32,573
when I say the name

817
00:41:32,615 --> 00:41:34,284
-Biggus
-[squeaks]

818
00:41:36,035 --> 00:41:37,162
Dickus?

819
00:41:37,203 --> 00:41:39,122
[snickers]

820
00:41:43,251 --> 00:41:45,544
[snickering continues]

821
00:41:56,764 --> 00:41:59,184
He has a wife, you know.

822
00:42:00,435 --> 00:42:02,520
You know what she's called?

823
00:42:05,648 --> 00:42:07,775
She's called...

824
00:42:07,817 --> 00:42:09,902
Incontinentia.

825
00:42:11,946 --> 00:42:13,614
-Incontinentia Buttocks.
-[uncontrollable laughter]

826
00:42:13,656 --> 00:42:15,825
Shut up!
What is all this?

827
00:42:15,867 --> 00:42:20,246
-[soldiers cackling]
-I've had enough of this rowdy,
rebel, sniggering behavior!

828
00:42:20,288 --> 00:42:23,458
Silence! You call yourselves
centurion guards?

829
00:42:23,500 --> 00:42:25,543
Seize him! Seize him!

830
00:42:25,584 --> 00:42:27,462
Blow your noses
and seize him!

831
00:42:27,504 --> 00:42:29,381
[dramatic music]

832
00:42:40,599 --> 00:42:43,311
Hmm? Oh.

833
00:42:49,484 --> 00:42:51,736
[whistling]

834
00:43:04,707 --> 00:43:07,419
Ahh!

835
00:43:16,302 --> 00:43:19,097
[speaking alien language]

836
00:43:19,138 --> 00:43:22,434
[alarm blares]

837
00:43:22,475 --> 00:43:24,519
[dramatic music continues]

838
00:43:50,711 --> 00:43:51,837
[brakes squeal]

839
00:44:13,568 --> 00:44:15,612
[spaceship descending]

840
00:44:15,653 --> 00:44:17,696
[crashing]

841
00:44:25,079 --> 00:44:27,790
You lucky bastard.

842
00:44:32,253 --> 00:44:34,046
[dramatic music resumes]

843
00:44:43,473 --> 00:44:46,976
And the beast's head
shall be huge and black

844
00:44:47,018 --> 00:44:49,228
and the eyes,
they're of red,

845
00:44:49,270 --> 00:44:51,523
with the blood
of living creatures!

846
00:44:51,564 --> 00:44:55,568
And the whore of Babylon
shall ride forth

847
00:44:55,610 --> 00:44:57,736
on a three-headed serpent

848
00:44:57,778 --> 00:45:02,659
and throughout the land shall
be a great rubbing of parts.

849
00:45:02,699 --> 00:45:07,372
And the demon shall bear
a nine-bladed sword!

850
00:45:07,413 --> 00:45:12,001
Nine-bladed! Not two
or five or seven, but nine!

851
00:45:12,043 --> 00:45:14,629
Which he will wield
on all wretched sinners.

852
00:45:14,671 --> 00:45:16,797
Sinners just like you,
sir, there.

853
00:45:16,839 --> 00:45:18,841
And the horns
shall be on the head...

854
00:45:18,883 --> 00:45:21,177
Through Hebediah,
his servant,

855
00:45:21,219 --> 00:45:26,224
there shall in that time
be rumors of things going astray

856
00:45:26,265 --> 00:45:30,811
and there shall be
a great confusion as to
where things really are.

857
00:45:30,853 --> 00:45:35,274
And nobody will really know
where lieth those little things

858
00:45:35,316 --> 00:45:39,778
with the sort of raffia-work
base, that has an attachment.

859
00:45:39,820 --> 00:45:45,410
At this time, a friend shall
lose his friend's hammer

860
00:45:45,451 --> 00:45:48,329
and the young shall not
know where lieth

861
00:45:48,371 --> 00:45:50,498
the things possessed
by their fathers

862
00:45:50,540 --> 00:45:54,586
that their fathers put there
only just the night before,
about 8:00.

863
00:45:54,627 --> 00:45:57,547
Yea, it is written
in the Book of Cyril

864
00:45:57,589 --> 00:45:59,840
that in that time
shall the turds...

865
00:45:59,882 --> 00:46:01,884
[indistinct chattering]

866
00:46:10,101 --> 00:46:12,103
-How much? Quickly.
-What?

867
00:46:12,144 --> 00:46:13,229
It's for the wife.

868
00:46:13,271 --> 00:46:15,940
Oh. Uh... twenty shekels.

869
00:46:15,981 --> 00:46:17,442
-Right.
-What?

870
00:46:17,483 --> 00:46:19,527
-There you are.
-Wait a minute.

871
00:46:19,569 --> 00:46:21,613
-What?
-Well, we're supposed to haggle.

872
00:46:21,654 --> 00:46:23,864
-No, no, no. I've got to--
-What do you mean,
"No, no, no"?

873
00:46:23,906 --> 00:46:25,450
-I haven't got time--
-Give it back then.

874
00:46:25,491 --> 00:46:27,201
-No, no, no, I just paid you.
-Burt.

875
00:46:27,243 --> 00:46:29,370
-Yeah?
-This bloke won't haggle.

876
00:46:29,412 --> 00:46:32,498
-Won't haggle?!
-All right, do we have to?

877
00:46:32,540 --> 00:46:35,418
-Now, look, I want 20 for that.
-I just gave you 20.

878
00:46:35,460 --> 00:46:37,253
Now, are you telling me
that's not worth 20 shekels?

879
00:46:37,295 --> 00:46:38,755
-No.
-Look at it.

880
00:46:38,795 --> 00:46:40,673
Feel the quality,
that's none of your goat.

881
00:46:40,715 --> 00:46:42,174
All right,
I'll give you 19 then.

882
00:46:42,216 --> 00:46:43,842
No, no, no.
Come on, do it properly.

883
00:46:43,884 --> 00:46:46,262
-What?
-Haggle properly,
this isn't worth 19.

884
00:46:46,304 --> 00:46:47,722
Well, you just said
it was worth 20.

885
00:46:47,764 --> 00:46:49,307
Oh, dear, oh, dear.

886
00:46:49,348 --> 00:46:51,684
-Come on, haggle.
-All right, I'll give you ten.

887
00:46:51,726 --> 00:46:55,062
That's more like it. Ten?
Are you trying to insult me?

888
00:46:55,104 --> 00:46:58,190
Me, with a poor,
dying grandmother? Ten?

889
00:46:58,232 --> 00:47:00,817
-All right, I'll give you 11.
-Now you're getting it, 11?!

890
00:47:00,859 --> 00:47:03,028
Did I hear you right?
Eleven?

891
00:47:03,070 --> 00:47:05,364
This cost me 12,
you want to ruin me?

892
00:47:05,406 --> 00:47:07,908
-Seventeen?
-No, no, no, no, "17"!

893
00:47:07,950 --> 00:47:10,745
-Eighteen?
-No, no, you go to 14 now.

894
00:47:10,787 --> 00:47:13,748
-All right, I'll give you 14.
-Fourteen!? Are you joking?

895
00:47:13,790 --> 00:47:15,832
-That's what you told me to say!
-Oh, dear.

896
00:47:15,874 --> 00:47:18,252
Tell me what to say, please!

897
00:47:18,294 --> 00:47:20,463
-Offer me 14.
-I'll give you 14.

898
00:47:20,505 --> 00:47:23,299
-He's offering me 14 for this!
-Fifteen!

899
00:47:23,341 --> 00:47:26,885
Seventeen. My last word,
I won't take a penny less,
or strike me dead.

900
00:47:26,927 --> 00:47:28,262
-Sixteen.
-Done.

901
00:47:29,681 --> 00:47:31,182
Nice to do business with you.

902
00:47:31,223 --> 00:47:32,725
Tell you what,
I'll throw you in this as well.

903
00:47:32,767 --> 00:47:34,352
-I don't want it, but thanks.
-Burt.

904
00:47:34,393 --> 00:47:36,521
-Yeah.
-All right,
all right, all right.

905
00:47:36,562 --> 00:47:38,939
-Now, where's the 16 you owe me?
-I just gave you 20.

906
00:47:38,981 --> 00:47:40,941
Oh, yeah, that's right.
That's four I owe you then.

907
00:47:40,983 --> 00:47:42,360
No, that's all right,
that's fine.

908
00:47:42,401 --> 00:47:43,695
No, hang on.
I've got it here somewhere.

909
00:47:43,736 --> 00:47:45,279
It's all right,
that's four for the gourd.

910
00:47:45,321 --> 00:47:47,114
Four? For this gourd?

911
00:47:47,156 --> 00:47:50,034
Four!? Look at it, it's worth
ten if it's worth a shekel!

912
00:47:50,075 --> 00:47:51,994
You just gave it
to me for nothing.

913
00:47:52,036 --> 00:47:53,621
Yes, but it's worth ten.

914
00:47:53,663 --> 00:47:57,583
All right, all right.

915
00:47:57,625 --> 00:48:01,629
No, no, no, no,
it's not worth ten,
you're supposed to argue.

916
00:48:01,671 --> 00:48:04,382
"Ten for that? You must be mad!"

917
00:48:06,592 --> 00:48:09,220
Oh, well.
One born every minute.

918
00:48:10,304 --> 00:48:12,181
-Daniel.
-Daniel.

919
00:48:12,223 --> 00:48:13,683
-Job.
-Job.

920
00:48:13,725 --> 00:48:15,393
-Job.
-Joshua.

921
00:48:15,434 --> 00:48:16,811
-Joshua.
-Joshua.

922
00:48:16,853 --> 00:48:17,936
-Judges.
-Judges.

923
00:48:17,978 --> 00:48:19,772
-Judges.
-And Brian.

924
00:48:19,814 --> 00:48:22,358
-And Brian.
-And Brian.

925
00:48:22,400 --> 00:48:26,278
I now propose that all seven
of these ex-brothers

926
00:48:26,320 --> 00:48:29,948
be now entered in the minutes
as probationary martyrs
to the cause.

927
00:48:29,990 --> 00:48:33,703
-I second that, Reg.
-Thank you, Loretta. On the nod.

928
00:48:33,745 --> 00:48:37,749
Siblings,
let us not be down-hearted.

929
00:48:37,790 --> 00:48:42,754
One total catastrophe like this
is just the beginning!

930
00:48:42,795 --> 00:48:45,840
Their glorious deaths
shall unite us all in a--

931
00:48:45,882 --> 00:48:46,674
Look out!

932
00:48:46,716 --> 00:48:49,301
[dramatic music]]

933
00:48:59,061 --> 00:49:02,147
Hello? Matthias?

934
00:49:03,566 --> 00:49:05,902
-Reg.
-[Reg whispers] Go away.

935
00:49:07,069 --> 00:49:08,905
Reg, it's me, Brian.

936
00:49:08,945 --> 00:49:10,907
Get off. Get off, out of it.

937
00:49:10,947 --> 00:49:12,283
-Stan?
-Piss off.

938
00:49:12,324 --> 00:49:14,535
-Yeah, piss off.
-[Reg] Bugger off.

939
00:49:14,577 --> 00:49:16,120
[loud knocking]

940
00:49:16,161 --> 00:49:19,373
Oh, shit!

941
00:49:20,458 --> 00:49:22,501
Coming.

942
00:49:22,543 --> 00:49:26,881
[knocking continues]

943
00:49:26,923 --> 00:49:30,635
[man] Yea, verily at that time,
which is written
in the Book of Obadiah,

944
00:49:30,676 --> 00:49:35,222
a man shall strike his donkey
and his nephew's donkey,

945
00:49:35,264 --> 00:49:38,476
and anyone in the vicinity of
either the nephew or the donkey.

946
00:49:38,517 --> 00:49:41,978
[Matthias] My eyes are dim,
I cannot see.

947
00:49:42,020 --> 00:49:44,022
-Are you Matthias?
-Yes.

948
00:49:44,064 --> 00:49:47,151
We have reason to believe
you may be hiding one
Brian of Nazareth,

949
00:49:47,192 --> 00:49:50,822
a member of
the terrorist organization
the People's Front of Judea.

950
00:49:50,863 --> 00:49:55,493
Me? No, I'm just a poor old man,
I have no time for lawbreakers.

951
00:49:55,534 --> 00:49:57,994
My legs are grey,
my ears are nulled,

952
00:49:58,036 --> 00:50:00,790
-my eyes are old and bent--
-Quiet!

953
00:50:00,832 --> 00:50:04,293
Silly person.
Guards, search the house.

954
00:50:14,887 --> 00:50:19,391
You know the penalty
laid down by Roman law
for harboring a known criminal?

955
00:50:19,433 --> 00:50:21,393
-No.
-Crucifixion.

956
00:50:21,435 --> 00:50:22,561
Oh.

957
00:50:24,396 --> 00:50:25,731
Nasty, eh?

958
00:50:25,773 --> 00:50:27,566
It could be worse.

959
00:50:27,608 --> 00:50:30,026
What do you mean,
"could be worse"?

960
00:50:30,068 --> 00:50:32,363
Well, you could be
stabbed.

961
00:50:32,404 --> 00:50:34,532
Stabbed?
It takes a second.

962
00:50:34,573 --> 00:50:38,619
Crucifixion lasts hours.
It's a slow, horrible death.

963
00:50:38,661 --> 00:50:42,206
Well, at least it gets you
out in the open air.

964
00:50:43,290 --> 00:50:44,834
You're weird.

965
00:50:52,758 --> 00:50:56,094
No, sir,
couldn't find anything, sir.

966
00:50:56,136 --> 00:51:00,016
Well, don't worry, you've not
seen the last of us... weirdo.

967
00:51:00,056 --> 00:51:02,267
-Big nose.
-Watch it!

968
00:51:04,854 --> 00:51:07,147
Whew! That was lucky.

969
00:51:11,109 --> 00:51:12,528
I'm sorry, Reg.

970
00:51:12,570 --> 00:51:15,239
Oh, it's all right.
Siblings, he's sorry.

971
00:51:15,280 --> 00:51:18,074
He's sorry he led
the Fifth legion straight to
our official headquarters.

972
00:51:18,116 --> 00:51:19,785
Well, that's all right then,
Brian.

973
00:51:19,827 --> 00:51:23,079
Sit down! Have a scone.
Make yourself at home.

974
00:51:23,121 --> 00:51:24,916
You klutz!

975
00:51:24,957 --> 00:51:28,293
You stupid, birdbrained,
flat-headed--

976
00:51:28,335 --> 00:51:30,128
[loud knocking]

977
00:51:32,965 --> 00:51:35,509
[man continues] ...with a great
juicy melon behind.

978
00:51:35,551 --> 00:51:37,177
[knocking continues]

979
00:51:37,219 --> 00:51:40,514
My legs are old and bent,
my ears are grizzled, yes?

980
00:51:40,556 --> 00:51:43,475
There's one place
we didn't look.

981
00:51:43,517 --> 00:51:45,310
-Guards!
-I'm just a poor old man,

982
00:51:45,352 --> 00:51:50,106
my sight is dim, my eyes are
poor, my nose is knackered.

983
00:51:50,148 --> 00:51:52,944
Have you ever seen
anyone crucified?

984
00:51:52,985 --> 00:51:55,780
Crucifixion's a doddle.

985
00:51:55,821 --> 00:51:57,823
Don't keep saying that.

986
00:52:02,244 --> 00:52:04,580
Found this spoon, sir.

987
00:52:04,622 --> 00:52:06,540
Well done, sergeant.

988
00:52:07,625 --> 00:52:10,669
We'll be back...
oddball.

989
00:52:13,089 --> 00:52:15,633
-[loud knocking]
-[man] Open up.

990
00:52:15,674 --> 00:52:18,260
You haven't given us
time to hide.

991
00:52:18,302 --> 00:52:20,304
Ahh!

992
00:52:20,345 --> 00:52:22,765
Whoa!

993
00:52:29,605 --> 00:52:33,442
[both shouting]

994
00:52:33,484 --> 00:52:36,695
[both preaching]

995
00:52:42,076 --> 00:52:44,870
Don't pass judgment
on other people,

996
00:52:44,912 --> 00:52:47,123
or you might get
judged yourself.

997
00:52:47,163 --> 00:52:48,624
What?

998
00:52:48,666 --> 00:52:50,626
I said, don't pass judgment
on other people

999
00:52:50,668 --> 00:52:53,169
or else you might
get judged too.

1000
00:52:53,211 --> 00:52:55,255
-Who, me?
-Yes.

1001
00:52:55,297 --> 00:52:56,757
Oh, thank you very much.

1002
00:52:56,799 --> 00:52:58,843
Well, not just you,
all of you.

1003
00:52:58,884 --> 00:53:01,261
-That's a nice gourd.
-What?

1004
00:53:01,303 --> 00:53:03,430
-How much do you want
for the gourd?
-You can have it.

1005
00:53:03,472 --> 00:53:06,058
-Have it?
-Yes. Consider the lilies.

1006
00:53:06,100 --> 00:53:08,853
-Don't you want to haggle?
-No. In the field.

1007
00:53:08,894 --> 00:53:11,147
-What's wrong with it, then?
-Nothing, take it.

1008
00:53:11,187 --> 00:53:14,358
-Consider the lilies?
-Well, the birds, then.

1009
00:53:14,399 --> 00:53:15,943
-What birds?
-Any birds.

1010
00:53:15,985 --> 00:53:19,155
-Why?
-Well, have they got jobs?

1011
00:53:19,195 --> 00:53:21,239
-Who?
-The birds.

1012
00:53:21,281 --> 00:53:22,741
Have the birds got jobs?!

1013
00:53:22,783 --> 00:53:24,493
What's the matter
with him?

1014
00:53:24,535 --> 00:53:26,286
He says the birds
are scrounging.

1015
00:53:26,328 --> 00:53:29,540
No, the point is the birds,
they do all right, don't they?

1016
00:53:29,581 --> 00:53:32,501
-Well, and good luck to them!
-Yeah, they're very pretty.

1017
00:53:32,543 --> 00:53:36,839
Okay. And you're much more
important than they are, right?

1018
00:53:36,881 --> 00:53:39,383
So, what are you worrying about?
There you are! See?

1019
00:53:39,424 --> 00:53:42,011
I'm worrying about what
you've got against birds.

1020
00:53:42,053 --> 00:53:45,347
I haven't got anything against
birds. Consider lilies--

1021
00:53:45,389 --> 00:53:47,349
He's having a go
at the flowers now.

1022
00:53:47,391 --> 00:53:49,643
-Give the flowers a chance.
-I'll give you one for it.

1023
00:53:49,685 --> 00:53:51,436
-It's yours!
-Two then.

1024
00:53:51,478 --> 00:53:54,899
[sighs] Look, there was this
man, and he had two servants--

1025
00:53:54,940 --> 00:53:56,274
-What were they called?
-What?

1026
00:53:56,316 --> 00:53:58,610
-What were their names?
-I don't know.

1027
00:53:58,652 --> 00:54:00,071
And he gave them
some talents--

1028
00:54:00,112 --> 00:54:02,656
-You don't know?
-Well, it doesn't matter.

1029
00:54:02,698 --> 00:54:04,658
He doesn't know
what they were called!

1030
00:54:04,700 --> 00:54:06,577
Oh, they were called
Simon and Adrian. Now--

1031
00:54:06,618 --> 00:54:08,787
You said you didn't know!

1032
00:54:08,829 --> 00:54:11,165
It really doesn't matter,
the point is there were
these two servants--

1033
00:54:11,207 --> 00:54:13,458
He's making it up
as he goes along!

1034
00:54:13,500 --> 00:54:15,211
No, I'm not!
And he gave them--

1035
00:54:15,251 --> 00:54:17,046
-Wait a minute,
were there three?
-[all groan]

1036
00:54:17,088 --> 00:54:20,465
-He's terrible.
-There were three
stewards really.

1037
00:54:20,507 --> 00:54:22,176
[woman] Oh, get off!

1038
00:54:28,766 --> 00:54:30,434
Now--Now, hear this.

1039
00:54:30,475 --> 00:54:33,812
Blessed are they who convert
their neighbor's ox,

1040
00:54:33,854 --> 00:54:36,607
for they shall
inhibit their girth.

1041
00:54:36,648 --> 00:54:39,401
-[man] Rubbish!
-And, to them only,

1042
00:54:39,443 --> 00:54:42,113
shall be given...

1043
00:54:42,154 --> 00:54:45,116
To them only

1044
00:54:45,157 --> 00:54:48,619
shall be given...

1045
00:54:50,246 --> 00:54:51,705
-[woman] What?
-Hmm?

1046
00:54:51,747 --> 00:54:54,666
-[woman] Shall be given what?
-Oh, nothing.

1047
00:54:54,708 --> 00:54:56,543
-What were you going to say?
-[Brian] Nothing.

1048
00:54:56,585 --> 00:54:57,920
Yes, you were going
to say something.

1049
00:54:57,962 --> 00:54:59,880
-No, I wasn't. I finished.
-Oh, no, no.

1050
00:54:59,922 --> 00:55:01,799
Come on,
tell us before you go.

1051
00:55:01,840 --> 00:55:03,842
-I wasn't going to say anything.
I finished.
-[woman] No, you hadn't.

1052
00:55:03,884 --> 00:55:05,844
-What won't he tell us?
-He won't say.

1053
00:55:05,886 --> 00:55:07,387
-Is it a secret?
-No.

1054
00:55:07,429 --> 00:55:09,514
-Is it?
-It must be,
otherwise he'd tell us.

1055
00:55:09,556 --> 00:55:11,391
-Oh, tell us the secret.
-Leave me alone.

1056
00:55:11,433 --> 00:55:14,019
-What is the secret?
-Is it the secret
of eternal life?

1057
00:55:14,061 --> 00:55:15,687
-He won't say!
-Of course not!

1058
00:55:15,729 --> 00:55:17,982
If I knew the secret
of eternal life,
I wouldn't say.

1059
00:55:18,023 --> 00:55:19,942
-Leave me alone.
-Just tell me, please.

1060
00:55:19,984 --> 00:55:21,693
No, tell us, master,
we were here first.

1061
00:55:21,735 --> 00:55:22,694
[all clamoring]

1062
00:55:22,736 --> 00:55:24,655
-Five!
-Go away!

1063
00:55:24,696 --> 00:55:26,531
-Tell us, master.
-I can't go above five.

1064
00:55:26,573 --> 00:55:29,493
-Is that his gourd?
-Yes, but it's under offer.

1065
00:55:29,534 --> 00:55:33,164
-This is his gourd.
-Ten!

1066
00:55:33,205 --> 00:55:35,040
It is his gourd.

1067
00:55:35,082 --> 00:55:38,085
We will carry it for you,
master.

1068
00:55:38,127 --> 00:55:40,129
Master?

1069
00:55:40,171 --> 00:55:43,007
He's gone.
He's been taken up.

1070
00:55:43,048 --> 00:55:47,343
-Oh, he has been taken up!
-Eighteen!

1071
00:55:47,385 --> 00:55:49,096
No, there he is.
Over there.

1072
00:55:49,138 --> 00:55:52,348
[clamoring resumes]

1073
00:55:52,390 --> 00:55:55,102
[dramatic music]

1074
00:56:14,997 --> 00:56:16,999
Look! Look!

1075
00:56:17,041 --> 00:56:19,084
-[gasps]
-He has given us a sign.

1076
00:56:19,126 --> 00:56:21,837
He has given us his shoe!

1077
00:56:21,879 --> 00:56:24,464
The shoe is the sign!
Let us follow his example!

1078
00:56:24,506 --> 00:56:27,051
-What?
-Let us, like him,

1079
00:56:27,092 --> 00:56:29,928
hold up one shoe and let
the other be upon our foot,

1080
00:56:29,970 --> 00:56:33,724
for this is his sign
that all who follow him
shall do likewise!

1081
00:56:33,765 --> 00:56:35,809
No, no, the shoe is a sign

1082
00:56:35,851 --> 00:56:39,063
that we must gather shoes
together in abundance.

1083
00:56:39,104 --> 00:56:41,606
Cast off the shoes.
Follow the gourd!

1084
00:56:41,648 --> 00:56:44,193
No, let us gather
shoes together.

1085
00:56:44,235 --> 00:56:46,320
-Let me!
-Oh, get off!

1086
00:56:46,362 --> 00:56:49,323
No, it is a sign that, like him,
we must think not of
the things of the body,

1087
00:56:49,365 --> 00:56:51,075
but of the face and head!

1088
00:56:51,116 --> 00:56:54,119
-Give me your shoe!
-Get off!

1089
00:56:54,161 --> 00:56:57,622
Follow the gourd,
the holy gourd of Jerusalem!

1090
00:56:57,664 --> 00:56:58,916
The gourd!

1091
00:56:58,957 --> 00:57:00,918
Hold up the sandal,
like he has--

1092
00:57:00,959 --> 00:57:03,419
-It is a shoe! It is a shoe!
-It's a sandal!

1093
00:57:03,461 --> 00:57:06,673
-No, it isn't! It is a shoe!
-[woman] Cast it away!

1094
00:57:06,715 --> 00:57:08,342
-Put it on!
-Now clear off.

1095
00:57:08,384 --> 00:57:10,719
Take the shoes and follow him!

1096
00:57:10,761 --> 00:57:14,514
Come all ye who call
yourselves Gourdenes.

1097
00:57:14,556 --> 00:57:17,059
[clamoring resumes]

1098
00:57:17,101 --> 00:57:18,769
Stop, I say.

1099
00:57:18,810 --> 00:57:21,438
Stop. Let us...

1100
00:57:22,522 --> 00:57:24,649
Let us pray.

1101
00:57:24,691 --> 00:57:27,652
Yea, he cometh to us

1102
00:57:27,694 --> 00:57:30,322
like the seed to the grave...

1103
00:57:38,414 --> 00:57:41,166
[dramatic music]

1104
00:57:50,884 --> 00:57:52,928
[clamoring continues]

1105
00:57:52,970 --> 00:57:55,973
Master! Master!

1106
00:57:56,014 --> 00:57:59,684
[music continues]

1107
00:58:17,577 --> 00:58:21,248
Hey, is there
another way down?

1108
00:58:21,290 --> 00:58:24,335
Is there another path
down to the river?

1109
00:58:24,376 --> 00:58:25,919
[grunting]

1110
00:58:25,961 --> 00:58:28,088
Please, please, help me!
I've got to get...

1111
00:58:28,130 --> 00:58:30,674
[all clamoring]

1112
00:58:32,301 --> 00:58:33,385
Oh, my foot!

1113
00:58:33,427 --> 00:58:35,595
-[groans]
-[shushing]

1114
00:58:35,637 --> 00:58:38,640
-Damn! Damn! Damn!
-I'm sorry.

1115
00:58:38,682 --> 00:58:42,519
-Oh, damn! Damn and blast it!
-I'm sorry! Shh!

1116
00:58:42,560 --> 00:58:43,979
Don't you "shh" me.

1117
00:58:44,021 --> 00:58:47,024
Eighteen years of total silence,
and you "shh" me.

1118
00:58:47,065 --> 00:58:50,277
-What?
-I've kept my vow for 18 years.

1119
00:58:50,319 --> 00:58:53,197
Not a single recognizable,
articulate sound

1120
00:58:53,238 --> 00:58:54,823
has passed my lips.

1121
00:58:54,865 --> 00:58:56,616
Oh, please, could you be quiet
for another five minutes?

1122
00:58:56,658 --> 00:58:59,536
Oh, it doesn't matter now,
I might as well enjoy myself.

1123
00:58:59,577 --> 00:59:03,374
The times in the last 18 years
I wanted to shout and sing

1124
00:59:03,415 --> 00:59:06,584
-and scream my name out!
Oh, I'm alive!
-Shh! Shh!

1125
00:59:06,626 --> 00:59:12,508
<i>♪ Hava nagila hava nagila</i>
<i>Hava nagila-- ♪</i>

1126
00:59:12,549 --> 00:59:14,009
[mumbling]

1127
00:59:14,051 --> 00:59:15,593
Oh, I'm alive! I'm alive!

1128
00:59:15,635 --> 00:59:18,930
Hello, birds! Hello, trees!
I'm alive!

1129
00:59:18,972 --> 00:59:20,265
Get off! I'm alive!

1130
00:59:20,307 --> 00:59:24,311
[singing]

1131
00:59:25,396 --> 00:59:29,774
[all] Master! Master!

1132
00:59:29,816 --> 00:59:32,403
The master! He is here!

1133
00:59:32,444 --> 00:59:34,405
-His shoe!
-It was the gourd!

1134
00:59:34,446 --> 00:59:35,697
[clamoring]

1135
00:59:35,739 --> 00:59:37,449
The shoe has brought us!

1136
00:59:37,491 --> 00:59:40,702
Speak! Speak to us, master!
Speak to us!

1137
00:59:40,744 --> 00:59:42,413
Go away!

1138
00:59:42,454 --> 00:59:45,541
[all] A blessing! A blessing!

1139
00:59:45,582 --> 00:59:47,709
How shall we go away, master?

1140
00:59:47,751 --> 00:59:50,170
Just go away and leave me alone.

1141
00:59:50,212 --> 00:59:52,214
Give us a sign.

1142
00:59:52,256 --> 00:59:55,759
He has given us a sign,
he has brought us to this place!

1143
00:59:55,800 --> 00:59:58,470
I didn't bring you here,
you just followed me!

1144
00:59:58,512 --> 01:00:01,557
Oh, it's still a good sign,
by any standard.

1145
01:00:01,598 --> 01:00:04,851
Master, your people have walked
many miles to be with you.

1146
01:00:04,893 --> 01:00:06,644
They are weary
and have not eaten.

1147
01:00:06,686 --> 01:00:08,897
It's not my fault
they haven't eaten!

1148
01:00:08,939 --> 01:00:11,358
There is no food
in this high mountain.

1149
01:00:11,400 --> 01:00:14,945
What about the juniper bushes
over there?

1150
01:00:14,986 --> 01:00:18,990
[all gasp] A miracle! A miracle!

1151
01:00:19,032 --> 01:00:22,578
He has made the bush
fruitful by his word!

1152
01:00:22,619 --> 01:00:24,746
They brought forth
juniper berries!

1153
01:00:24,788 --> 01:00:27,832
Of course they brought forth
juniper berries,
they're juniper bushes.

1154
01:00:27,874 --> 01:00:31,002
-What do you expect?!
-Show us another miracle.

1155
01:00:31,044 --> 01:00:33,213
Do not tempt him,
shallow ones!

1156
01:00:33,255 --> 01:00:37,217
Is not the miracle
of the juniper bushes enough?

1157
01:00:37,259 --> 01:00:39,511
I say, those are
my juniper bushes.

1158
01:00:39,553 --> 01:00:41,179
They are a gift
from God!

1159
01:00:41,221 --> 01:00:43,265
They're all I've
bloody got to eat.

1160
01:00:43,307 --> 01:00:46,184
[grunts] I say, get off
of those bushes! Go on!

1161
01:00:46,226 --> 01:00:48,479
Clear off, the lot of you.

1162
01:00:48,520 --> 01:00:52,649
Lord, I am affected
by a bald patch.

1163
01:00:52,690 --> 01:00:56,320
I'm healed!
The master has healed me!

1164
01:00:56,361 --> 01:00:57,529
I didn't touch him!

1165
01:00:57,571 --> 01:01:00,198
I was blind,
and now I can see!

1166
01:01:00,240 --> 01:01:04,495
[all] A miracle!
A miracle! A miracle!

1167
01:01:04,536 --> 01:01:06,204
[chattering]

1168
01:01:06,246 --> 01:01:07,872
Tell them to stop it.

1169
01:01:07,914 --> 01:01:10,917
I hadn't said a word
for 18 years till he came along.

1170
01:01:10,959 --> 01:01:14,963
[all] A miracle!
He is the Messiah!

1171
01:01:15,005 --> 01:01:16,548
And he hurt my foot!

1172
01:01:16,590 --> 01:01:20,177
[all] Hurt my foot, Lord!
Hurt mine! Hurt mine!

1173
01:01:20,218 --> 01:01:23,972
-Hail Messiah!
-I'm not the Messiah!

1174
01:01:24,014 --> 01:01:27,559
I say you are, Lord.
And I should know,
I've followed a few!

1175
01:01:27,601 --> 01:01:29,978
[all] Hail Messiah!

1176
01:01:30,020 --> 01:01:32,189
I'm not the Messiah!
Would you please listen,

1177
01:01:32,230 --> 01:01:34,650
I am not the Messiah,
do you understand?

1178
01:01:34,691 --> 01:01:36,943
Honestly!

1179
01:01:36,985 --> 01:01:40,738
Only the true Messiah
denies his divinity.

1180
01:01:40,780 --> 01:01:44,034
What? Well, what sort of chance
does that give me?

1181
01:01:44,075 --> 01:01:46,203
All right, I am the Messiah!

1182
01:01:46,244 --> 01:01:50,248
[all] He is!
He is the Messiah!

1183
01:01:50,290 --> 01:01:52,959
Now, fuck off!

1184
01:02:00,342 --> 01:02:02,177
How shall we fuck off,
o Lord?

1185
01:02:02,219 --> 01:02:04,221
Oh, just go away!
Leave me alone!

1186
01:02:04,262 --> 01:02:07,224
You told these people
to eat my juniper berries.

1187
01:02:07,265 --> 01:02:10,227
You break my bloody foot,
you break my vow of silence

1188
01:02:10,268 --> 01:02:13,146
and then you try and clean up
on my juniper bushes!

1189
01:02:13,188 --> 01:02:16,941
Lay off! This is the Messiah,
the chosen one!

1190
01:02:16,983 --> 01:02:20,362
-No, he's not.
-An unbeliever!

1191
01:02:20,404 --> 01:02:21,779
[all] An unbeliever!

1192
01:02:21,821 --> 01:02:24,616
Persecute! Kill the heretic!

1193
01:02:24,658 --> 01:02:27,035
[all] Yeah! Kill! Kill! Kill!

1194
01:02:27,077 --> 01:02:30,247
-[all chanting] Kill!
-Leave him alone!

1195
01:02:30,288 --> 01:02:33,041
Leave him alone!

1196
01:02:33,083 --> 01:02:35,335
Leave him alone.

1197
01:02:35,377 --> 01:02:38,672
Put him down. Please!

1198
01:02:39,923 --> 01:02:42,300
[romantic music]

1199
01:02:42,342 --> 01:02:43,677
Brian?

1200
01:02:43,719 --> 01:02:45,345
Judith?

1201
01:02:49,849 --> 01:02:51,560
[man imitates rooster]
Cock-a-doodle-doo!

1202
01:02:51,602 --> 01:02:53,978
[romantic music continues]

1203
01:03:31,933 --> 01:03:34,018
[all] Look, there he is!

1204
01:03:34,060 --> 01:03:37,063
The chosen one has woken!

1205
01:03:39,065 --> 01:03:40,358
-[pounding on door]
-[mother] Brian!

1206
01:03:40,400 --> 01:03:41,652
[gasps]

1207
01:03:41,693 --> 01:03:43,027
Ooh! Mother!

1208
01:03:43,069 --> 01:03:46,239
-Brian!
-Hang on, Mother!

1209
01:03:47,824 --> 01:03:49,618
[door crashes open]

1210
01:03:49,660 --> 01:03:53,121
-Hello, Mother.
-Don't you "hello, Mother" me.

1211
01:03:53,163 --> 01:03:54,956
What are those people
doing out there?

1212
01:03:54,998 --> 01:03:56,416
Oh, well, I--

1213
01:03:56,458 --> 01:03:58,335
Come on! What have you
been up to, my lad?

1214
01:03:58,376 --> 01:04:00,878
I think they must have
popped by for something.

1215
01:04:00,920 --> 01:04:02,172
Popped by?!

1216
01:04:02,213 --> 01:04:04,090
Swarmed by, more like.

1217
01:04:04,132 --> 01:04:06,343
There's a multitude out there!

1218
01:04:06,384 --> 01:04:08,011
They started
following me yesterday.

1219
01:04:08,052 --> 01:04:11,306
Well, they can stop
following you right now.

1220
01:04:12,474 --> 01:04:14,810
Now stop following my son.

1221
01:04:14,851 --> 01:04:17,395
You ought to be
ashamed of yourselves.

1222
01:04:17,437 --> 01:04:21,983
[all] The Messiah! The Messiah!
Show us the Messiah!

1223
01:04:22,025 --> 01:04:25,737
-The who?
-[all] The Messiah!

1224
01:04:25,779 --> 01:04:27,405
There's no Messiah in here.

1225
01:04:27,447 --> 01:04:29,616
There's a mess all right,
but no Messiah.

1226
01:04:29,658 --> 01:04:30,950
Now go away!

1227
01:04:30,992 --> 01:04:33,161
[all chant] Brian! Brian!

1228
01:04:33,203 --> 01:04:35,747
Right, my lad,
what have you been up to?

1229
01:04:35,789 --> 01:04:37,915
-Nothing, Mum.
-Come on, out with it.

1230
01:04:37,957 --> 01:04:39,876
They think I'm the Messiah, Mum.

1231
01:04:39,917 --> 01:04:41,712
What have you been
telling them?

1232
01:04:41,753 --> 01:04:43,004
Nothing, I only--

1233
01:04:43,046 --> 01:04:44,130
You're only making it
worse for yourself.

1234
01:04:44,172 --> 01:04:45,757
Look, I can explain--

1235
01:04:45,799 --> 01:04:51,054
No, let me explain, Mrs. Cohen!
Your son is a born leader!

1236
01:04:51,095 --> 01:04:54,432
Those people out there are
following him because they
believe in him, Mrs. Cohen.

1237
01:04:54,474 --> 01:04:56,267
They believe he can
give them hope.

1238
01:04:56,309 --> 01:05:00,397
Hope of a new life,
a new world, a better future!

1239
01:05:02,524 --> 01:05:06,236
-Who's that!?
-Oh! That's Judith, Mum.

1240
01:05:06,277 --> 01:05:07,945
Judith, Mother.

1241
01:05:07,987 --> 01:05:11,408
Hmm. Ahh!

1242
01:05:11,449 --> 01:05:15,704
-Ooh...!
-[crowd chants] Show us
the Messiah!

1243
01:05:15,746 --> 01:05:18,582
Show us the Messiah!

1244
01:05:18,623 --> 01:05:21,918
Now you listen here,
he's not the Messiah!

1245
01:05:21,959 --> 01:05:25,338
He's a very naughty boy!
Now go away!

1246
01:05:25,380 --> 01:05:26,964
[all] Who are you?

1247
01:05:27,006 --> 01:05:29,551
I'm his mother, that's who.

1248
01:05:29,593 --> 01:05:33,971
[all] Behold his mother!
Behold his mother!

1249
01:05:34,013 --> 01:05:37,559
Hail to thee, mother of Brian!

1250
01:05:37,601 --> 01:05:41,354
Blessed art thou! Hosanna!

1251
01:05:41,396 --> 01:05:45,859
All things to thee,
now and always!

1252
01:05:45,901 --> 01:05:48,862
Now, don't think you can
get around me like that.

1253
01:05:48,904 --> 01:05:52,990
He's not coming out,
and that's my final word.

1254
01:05:54,075 --> 01:05:55,201
Now shove off!

1255
01:05:55,243 --> 01:05:57,704
[all] No!

1256
01:05:57,746 --> 01:05:59,873
Did you hear what I said?

1257
01:05:59,915 --> 01:06:01,332
[all] Yes!

1258
01:06:01,374 --> 01:06:04,294
Oh, I see.
It's like that, is it?

1259
01:06:04,335 --> 01:06:05,962
[all] Yes!

1260
01:06:06,003 --> 01:06:09,674
Oh, all right then, you can
see him for one minute,

1261
01:06:09,716 --> 01:06:12,594
but not one second more,
do you understand?

1262
01:06:12,636 --> 01:06:14,262
[all] Yes.

1263
01:06:14,304 --> 01:06:15,138
Promise?

1264
01:06:15,179 --> 01:06:19,100
[all] Well, all right.

1265
01:06:19,142 --> 01:06:20,852
All right, here he is then.

1266
01:06:20,894 --> 01:06:22,479
Come on, Brian,
come and talk to them.

1267
01:06:22,520 --> 01:06:25,231
-But, Mum, Judith--
-Leave that Welsh tart alone.

1268
01:06:25,273 --> 01:06:27,317
-I don't really want to, Mum.
-[crowd cheers]

1269
01:06:34,783 --> 01:06:35,784
[Brian] Good morning!

1270
01:06:35,826 --> 01:06:38,161
[all] A blessing! A blessing!

1271
01:06:38,202 --> 01:06:43,291
No, please.
Please, please, listen!

1272
01:06:43,333 --> 01:06:46,085
I've got one or two things
to say.

1273
01:06:46,127 --> 01:06:48,797
[all] Tell us!
Tell us both of them!

1274
01:06:48,839 --> 01:06:51,466
Look, you've got it all wrong!

1275
01:06:51,508 --> 01:06:53,885
You don't need to follow me.

1276
01:06:53,927 --> 01:06:57,555
You don't need to
follow anybody!

1277
01:06:57,597 --> 01:07:00,183
You've got to
think for yourselves.

1278
01:07:00,224 --> 01:07:02,727
You're all individuals!

1279
01:07:02,769 --> 01:07:06,356
[all] Yes, we're all
individuals!

1280
01:07:06,397 --> 01:07:08,358
You're all different.

1281
01:07:08,399 --> 01:07:11,528
[all] Yes, we are all different!

1282
01:07:11,569 --> 01:07:12,904
I'm not.

1283
01:07:12,946 --> 01:07:14,447
[crowd shushing]

1284
01:07:14,489 --> 01:07:18,075
You've all got to work it out
for yourselves!

1285
01:07:18,117 --> 01:07:22,413
[all] Yes, we've got to work it
out for ourselves!

1286
01:07:22,455 --> 01:07:24,791
Exactly!

1287
01:07:24,833 --> 01:07:26,626
[all] Tell us more!

1288
01:07:26,668 --> 01:07:31,172
No, that's the point! Don't let
anyone tell you what to do!

1289
01:07:31,214 --> 01:07:34,676
-Otherwise-- Oh, no!
-That's enough! That's enough.

1290
01:07:34,718 --> 01:07:36,636
[crowd boos]

1291
01:07:36,678 --> 01:07:39,222
[all] That wasn't a minute.

1292
01:07:40,390 --> 01:07:42,308
Oh, yes, it was.

1293
01:07:42,350 --> 01:07:44,811
[all] Oh, no, it wasn't!

1294
01:07:44,853 --> 01:07:47,731
Now stop that and go away.

1295
01:07:47,772 --> 01:07:50,066
-Excuse me?
-Yes?

1296
01:07:50,107 --> 01:07:52,360
Are you a virgin?

1297
01:07:52,402 --> 01:07:54,404
I beg your pardon?

1298
01:07:54,445 --> 01:07:58,909
Well, if it's not a personal
question, are you a virgin?

1299
01:07:58,950 --> 01:08:01,578
"If it's not a
personal question"?!

1300
01:08:01,619 --> 01:08:04,288
How much more
personal can you get?

1301
01:08:04,330 --> 01:08:06,457
Now piss off.

1302
01:08:07,876 --> 01:08:10,336
-She is.
-Must be. Definitely.

1303
01:08:10,378 --> 01:08:13,214
[all murmur in agreement]

1304
01:08:13,256 --> 01:08:14,716
[chattering]

1305
01:08:14,758 --> 01:08:17,510
-[all gasp]
-Morning, Savior!

1306
01:08:17,552 --> 01:08:20,096
[all clamoring]

1307
01:08:27,186 --> 01:08:29,397
Lay your hands on me! Quick!

1308
01:08:29,439 --> 01:08:32,901
[man] Now, don't jostle
the chosen one! Please!

1309
01:08:32,943 --> 01:08:35,946
Don't push that baby
in the Savior's face!

1310
01:08:35,987 --> 01:08:37,781
He'll touch it later!

1311
01:08:37,822 --> 01:08:41,325
I say, could he see my wife?
She has a headache.

1312
01:08:41,367 --> 01:08:43,036
You'll have to wait,
I'm afraid!

1313
01:08:43,078 --> 01:08:45,246
She's very bad, and we've got
a luncheon appointment.

1314
01:08:45,288 --> 01:08:46,957
Look, the lepers are queuing!

1315
01:08:46,998 --> 01:08:49,960
Her brother-in-law
is the ex-mayor of Gath.

1316
01:08:50,001 --> 01:08:54,089
Brian, can I introduce
the gentleman who's letting us
have the mounts on Sunday?

1317
01:08:54,130 --> 01:08:57,092
-[man] Hello.
-Don't push!

1318
01:08:57,133 --> 01:09:00,219
Now keep the noise down, please!

1319
01:09:00,261 --> 01:09:04,724
Those possessed by devils,
try and keep them under control
a bit, can't you?

1320
01:09:04,766 --> 01:09:07,560
Incurables, you'll just have
to wait for a few minutes.

1321
01:09:07,602 --> 01:09:12,315
Um... women taken in sin, line
up against that wall, will you?

1322
01:09:12,356 --> 01:09:15,192
[Judith] Brian?

1323
01:09:15,234 --> 01:09:17,612
Brian! You were fantastic!

1324
01:09:17,654 --> 01:09:19,405
You weren't so bad yourself.

1325
01:09:19,447 --> 01:09:21,240
No, what you said just now!

1326
01:09:21,282 --> 01:09:22,617
Quite extraordinary!

1327
01:09:22,659 --> 01:09:24,160
What? Oh, that. Was it?

1328
01:09:24,201 --> 01:09:26,245
We don't need any leaders!
You're so right!

1329
01:09:26,287 --> 01:09:28,623
Reg has been
dominating us for too long.

1330
01:09:28,665 --> 01:09:29,958
Well, yes--

1331
01:09:30,000 --> 01:09:32,168
It needed saying,
and you said it, Brian!

1332
01:09:32,209 --> 01:09:33,753
You're very attractive.

1333
01:09:33,795 --> 01:09:36,923
It's our revolution!
We can all do it together!

1334
01:09:36,965 --> 01:09:38,091
I think... I think--

1335
01:09:38,133 --> 01:09:39,425
We're all behind you, Brian!

1336
01:09:39,467 --> 01:09:41,970
The revolution
is in your hands!

1337
01:09:42,012 --> 01:09:45,264
What? No, that's not
what I meant at all!

1338
01:09:45,306 --> 01:09:47,892
You're fucking nicked,
me old beauty!

1339
01:09:47,934 --> 01:09:50,061
-[dramatic music]
-Right!

1340
01:09:56,985 --> 01:09:58,820
Stop it!

1341
01:09:58,862 --> 01:10:00,363
[groans]

1342
01:10:00,404 --> 01:10:03,741
Well, Brian, you've given us
a good run for our money.

1343
01:10:03,783 --> 01:10:04,993
A what?

1344
01:10:05,035 --> 01:10:07,411
And this time,

1345
01:10:07,453 --> 01:10:10,665
I guarantee you will not escape.

1346
01:10:10,707 --> 01:10:15,211
Guard... do we have any
crucifixions today?

1347
01:10:15,252 --> 01:10:18,965
A hundred and thirty-nine, sir.
Special celebration.
Passover, sir.

1348
01:10:19,007 --> 01:10:21,759
Right! Now we have 140!

1349
01:10:21,801 --> 01:10:23,219
Nice round number, eh, Biggus?

1350
01:10:23,260 --> 01:10:24,679
[chuckles]

1351
01:10:24,721 --> 01:10:27,140
-[crowd clamoring]
-Hail Caesar!

1352
01:10:27,182 --> 01:10:28,808
Hail!

1353
01:10:28,850 --> 01:10:30,601
The crowd outside are
getting a bit restless, sir.

1354
01:10:30,643 --> 01:10:32,937
Permission to disperse them,
please.

1355
01:10:32,979 --> 01:10:35,815
Disperse them? But I haven't
addressed them yet!

1356
01:10:35,857 --> 01:10:37,400
Uh, no, I know, sir, but--

1357
01:10:37,441 --> 01:10:39,652
My address is one of
the high points of Passover!

1358
01:10:39,694 --> 01:10:43,447
My friend, Biggus Dickus,
has come all the way
from Rome just to hear it!

1359
01:10:43,489 --> 01:10:45,867
-Hail Caesar!
-[lisping] Hail Caesar!

1360
01:10:45,909 --> 01:10:49,162
You're not...

1361
01:10:49,204 --> 01:10:53,374
You're not thinking of giving
it a miss this year, then, sir?

1362
01:10:53,416 --> 01:10:55,168
Give it a miss?!

1363
01:10:55,210 --> 01:10:57,962
Well, it's just that they're in
a rather funny mood today, sir.

1364
01:10:58,004 --> 01:11:00,798
Really, centurion!
I'm surprised to hear
a man like you

1365
01:11:00,840 --> 01:11:03,634
rattled by
a rabble of rowdy rebels.

1366
01:11:03,676 --> 01:11:06,637
-A bit thundery, sir.
-Take him away!

1367
01:11:06,679 --> 01:11:09,891
I'm a Roman!
I can prove it, honestly!

1368
01:11:09,933 --> 01:11:13,228
And crucify him well!

1369
01:11:13,269 --> 01:11:14,395
Biggus!

1370
01:11:15,772 --> 01:11:17,148
[stammers] I really wouldn't,
sir!

1371
01:11:17,190 --> 01:11:18,649
Out of the way, centurion!

1372
01:11:18,691 --> 01:11:20,317
Let me come with you, Pontius.

1373
01:11:20,359 --> 01:11:23,071
I may be of some assistance
if there is a sudden crisis!

1374
01:11:25,198 --> 01:11:26,991
Right! Now, item four,

1375
01:11:27,033 --> 01:11:29,410
attainment of world supremacy
within the next five years.

1376
01:11:29,452 --> 01:11:31,370
Uh, Francis, you've been
doing some work on this?

1377
01:11:31,412 --> 01:11:32,747
Yeah, thank you, Reg.

1378
01:11:32,789 --> 01:11:34,665
Well, quite frankly, siblings,

1379
01:11:34,707 --> 01:11:38,211
I think five years is optimistic
unless we can
smash the Roman Empire

1380
01:11:38,253 --> 01:11:39,503
within the next 12 months!

1381
01:11:39,545 --> 01:11:41,214
-Twelve months?
-Yeah, 12 months.

1382
01:11:41,256 --> 01:11:42,590
And let's face it,

1383
01:11:42,632 --> 01:11:45,135
as empires go,
this is the big one.

1384
01:11:45,176 --> 01:11:48,721
So we gotta get up off our asses
and stop just talking about it!

1385
01:11:48,763 --> 01:11:50,681
[all] Hear! Hear!

1386
01:11:50,723 --> 01:11:53,643
I agree! It's action
that counts, not words,
and we need action now!

1387
01:11:53,684 --> 01:11:55,019
[all] Hear! Hear!

1388
01:11:55,061 --> 01:11:56,729
You're right. We could
sit around here all day,

1389
01:11:56,771 --> 01:12:00,357
talking, passing resolutions,
making clever speeches,

1390
01:12:00,399 --> 01:12:02,777
it's not gonna shift
one Roman soldier!

1391
01:12:02,819 --> 01:12:04,779
So let's just stop
gabbing on about it!

1392
01:12:04,821 --> 01:12:07,448
It's completely pointless
and it's getting us nowhere!

1393
01:12:07,490 --> 01:12:08,783
[all] Right!

1394
01:12:08,825 --> 01:12:10,868
I agree! This is a complete
waste of time!

1395
01:12:10,910 --> 01:12:12,203
[dramatic music]

1396
01:12:12,245 --> 01:12:13,037
They've arrested Brian!

1397
01:12:13,079 --> 01:12:14,664
[all] What?

1398
01:12:14,705 --> 01:12:17,292
They've dragged him off!
They're gonna crucify him!

1399
01:12:17,333 --> 01:12:20,170
Right! This calls
for immediate discussion!

1400
01:12:20,211 --> 01:12:21,671
-Yes.
-What?!

1401
01:12:21,712 --> 01:12:22,880
-Immediate!
-Right!

1402
01:12:22,922 --> 01:12:24,590
-New motion?
-Completely new motion!

1403
01:12:24,632 --> 01:12:29,262
Uh, that, uh... that
there be immediate action...

1404
01:12:29,304 --> 01:12:30,721
Uh, once the vote
has been taken.

1405
01:12:30,763 --> 01:12:32,265
Obviously,
once the vote's been taken.

1406
01:12:32,307 --> 01:12:33,724
Can't act on a resolution
until you've voted--

1407
01:12:33,766 --> 01:12:36,186
-Reg, let's go now, please!
-Right! Right!

1408
01:12:36,227 --> 01:12:40,273
In the light of
fresh information
from sibling Judith...

1409
01:12:40,315 --> 01:12:42,859
-Not so fast, Reg.
-Reg, for God's sake!

1410
01:12:42,900 --> 01:12:45,028
It's perfectly simple!

1411
01:12:45,069 --> 01:12:47,989
All you've gotta do is
to go out of that door now

1412
01:12:48,031 --> 01:12:50,992
and try to stop the Romans
nailing him up!

1413
01:12:51,034 --> 01:12:52,618
It's happening, Reg!

1414
01:12:52,660 --> 01:12:55,079
Something's actually happening,
Reg!

1415
01:12:55,121 --> 01:12:57,665
Can't you understand?

1416
01:12:57,707 --> 01:12:59,292
[frustrated scream]

1417
01:13:02,170 --> 01:13:03,046
[all snicker]

1418
01:13:03,087 --> 01:13:04,547
Yeah, hello.

1419
01:13:04,588 --> 01:13:06,465
Another little ego trip
from the feminists.

1420
01:13:06,507 --> 01:13:08,718
-What?
-Oh, sorry, Loretta.

1421
01:13:08,759 --> 01:13:11,095
Uh... read that back,
would you?

1422
01:13:11,137 --> 01:13:13,514
[ominous music]

1423
01:13:24,567 --> 01:13:25,818
Next.

1424
01:13:25,860 --> 01:13:27,904
-Crucifixion?
-Yes.

1425
01:13:27,945 --> 01:13:32,200
Good. Out of the door, line on
the left, one cross each.

1426
01:13:32,242 --> 01:13:33,826
Next.

1427
01:13:33,868 --> 01:13:35,703
-Crucifixion?
-Mm-hmm.

1428
01:13:35,745 --> 01:13:41,125
Good. Out of the door, line on
the left, one cross each. Next.

1429
01:13:41,167 --> 01:13:43,544
-Crucifixion?
-Uh, no, freedom.

1430
01:13:43,586 --> 01:13:44,670
Hmm?

1431
01:13:44,712 --> 01:13:46,130
-What?
-Uh, freedom for me.

1432
01:13:46,172 --> 01:13:48,216
They said I hadn't done anything
so I could go free

1433
01:13:48,258 --> 01:13:50,385
and live on an island somewhere.

1434
01:13:50,426 --> 01:13:52,303
Oh. Oh, well,
that's jolly good.

1435
01:13:52,345 --> 01:13:53,888
Well, off you go, then.

1436
01:13:53,930 --> 01:13:55,932
No, I'm only pulling your leg.
It's crucifixion, really.

1437
01:13:55,973 --> 01:13:58,517
Oh. I see.
Very good, very good.

1438
01:13:58,559 --> 01:14:00,519
Well, out of the door.

1439
01:14:00,561 --> 01:14:02,313
Yeah, I know the way.
Out of the door, one cross each,
line on the left.

1440
01:14:02,355 --> 01:14:05,233
Line on the left.
Yes, thank you.

1441
01:14:05,275 --> 01:14:06,234
Crucifixion?

1442
01:14:06,276 --> 01:14:07,318
-Yes.
-Good.

1443
01:14:07,360 --> 01:14:09,112
[fanfare plays]

1444
01:14:09,153 --> 01:14:10,863
[crowd cheering]

1445
01:14:18,955 --> 01:14:21,291
[cheering stops]

1446
01:14:21,332 --> 01:14:24,419
[speech impediment]
People of Jerusalem!

1447
01:14:24,460 --> 01:14:25,878
[crowd snickers]

1448
