Thank you.

1572
01:20:23,653 --> 01:20:26,447
-Hey! Hey!
-What do you think you're doing?

1573
01:20:26,489 --> 01:20:27,948
Uh, it's not my cross--

1574
01:20:27,990 --> 01:20:30,451
Shut up and get on with it!
Come on!

1575
01:20:32,536 --> 01:20:34,204
He had you there, mate,
didn't he?

1576
01:20:34,246 --> 01:20:35,998
That'll teach you a lesson!

1577
01:20:37,583 --> 01:20:40,002
All right!

1578
01:20:40,043 --> 01:20:42,171
I will give you one more chance!

1579
01:20:42,212 --> 01:20:46,091
This time I want to hear
no Rubens,

1580
01:20:46,133 --> 01:20:48,552
no Reginalds,

1581
01:20:48,594 --> 01:20:52,055
no Rudolph
the Red-nosed Reindeers.

1582
01:20:52,097 --> 01:20:54,266
No Spencer Tracys!

1583
01:20:54,308 --> 01:20:55,976
Or we shall release no one!

1584
01:20:56,018 --> 01:20:59,104
-Release Brian!
-Oh, yeah, that's a good one!

1585
01:20:59,146 --> 01:21:02,983
[all] Release Brian!
Release Brian!

1586
01:21:03,025 --> 01:21:05,361
[all laughing]

1587
01:21:05,402 --> 01:21:07,196
Very well! That's it!

1588
01:21:07,237 --> 01:21:09,948
-Sir, we have got a Brian, sir.
-What?

1589
01:21:09,990 --> 01:21:11,992
You just sent him
for crucifixion, sir!

1590
01:21:12,034 --> 01:21:15,245
Wait! Wait! We do have a Brian.

1591
01:21:15,287 --> 01:21:17,247
Well, go and free him,
straight away!

1592
01:21:17,289 --> 01:21:18,833
Yes, sir. Yes, sir.

1593
01:21:21,043 --> 01:21:23,003
Very well.

1594
01:21:23,045 --> 01:21:26,882
I shall release Brian!

1595
01:21:26,923 --> 01:21:29,385
[ominous music]

1596
01:21:30,511 --> 01:21:31,846
Get a move on, there!

1597
01:21:31,887 --> 01:21:34,431
-Or what?
-Or you'll be in trouble!

1598
01:21:34,473 --> 01:21:38,769
Oh, dear. You mean I might
have to give up being crucified
in the afternoons?

1599
01:21:38,811 --> 01:21:41,605
-Shut up!
-That would be a blow,
wouldn't it?

1600
01:21:41,647 --> 01:21:43,482
I wouldn't have nothing to do!

1601
01:21:43,524 --> 01:21:45,484
Oh, thank you!

1602
01:21:48,487 --> 01:21:51,407
Have they gone?

1603
01:21:51,448 --> 01:21:55,244
We've got lumps of it
around the back.

1604
01:21:55,285 --> 01:21:56,871
What?

1605
01:21:56,912 --> 01:21:59,874
Oh, don't worry about
him sir, he's ma...

1606
01:21:59,915 --> 01:22:02,626
[stammers]

1607
01:22:03,919 --> 01:22:05,671
He's... He's mad, sir.

1608
01:22:05,713 --> 01:22:07,631
Have they gone?!

1609
01:22:08,883 --> 01:22:10,718
Oh... [stammers]

1610
01:22:17,641 --> 01:22:21,270
-Oh, come on.
-Yes, sir.

1611
01:22:21,311 --> 01:22:22,855
Anyway, get on
with the story.

1612
01:22:22,897 --> 01:22:26,316
Well, I just never really
liked them, so I just--

1613
01:22:26,358 --> 01:22:29,027
Right! The motion to get on with
it passed with one abstention.

1614
01:22:29,069 --> 01:22:31,781
I propose we go without further
ado. May I have a second?

1615
01:22:31,822 --> 01:22:33,990
-Let's just go.
-Yeah, all right.

1616
01:22:34,032 --> 01:22:36,326
[dramatic music]

1617
01:22:49,423 --> 01:22:51,634
-Bloody Romans!
-Watch it!

1618
01:22:51,675 --> 01:22:54,136
Still a few crosses left!

1619
01:22:54,177 --> 01:22:55,596
[music continues]

1620
01:22:55,638 --> 01:22:58,641
Up you go,
big nose!

1621
01:22:58,682 --> 01:23:00,601
I'll get you for this,
you bastard!

1622
01:23:00,643 --> 01:23:02,853
-Oh, yeah!
-Oh, yeah. Don't worry.

1623
01:23:02,895 --> 01:23:04,605
-I never forget a face.
-No?

1624
01:23:04,647 --> 01:23:09,151
I warn you. I'm gonna punch
you so hard, you Roman git!

1625
01:23:09,192 --> 01:23:11,445
Shut up,
you Jewish turd!

1626
01:23:11,487 --> 01:23:13,280
Who are you calling Jewish?

1627
01:23:13,322 --> 01:23:15,866
I'm not Jewish, I'm a Samaritan!

1628
01:23:15,908 --> 01:23:18,786
A Samaritan? This is supposed
to be a Jewish section!

1629
01:23:18,828 --> 01:23:22,706
It doesn't matter!
You're all gonna die
in a day or two!

1630
01:23:22,748 --> 01:23:26,293
