Samaritans around here.

1648
01:24:09,336 --> 01:24:10,671
Belt up!

1649
01:24:10,713 --> 01:24:12,422
Will you let me down
if he comes back?

1650
01:24:12,464 --> 01:24:15,175
Yeah, yeah, we'll let
you down. Next!

1651
01:24:15,217 --> 01:24:18,094
You don't have to do this!
You don't have to take orders!

1652
01:24:18,136 --> 01:24:20,556
I like orders.

1653
01:24:20,597 --> 01:24:22,641
[dramatic music]

1654
01:24:42,327 --> 01:24:44,872
See? Not so bad once you're up.

1655
01:24:46,248 --> 01:24:47,624
You're being rescued
then, are you?

1656
01:24:47,666 --> 01:24:49,668
It's a bit late
for that now, isn't it?

1657
01:24:49,710 --> 01:24:52,254
Oh, no, we've got
a couple of days up here.

1658
01:24:52,295 --> 01:24:54,339
Plenty of time.
Lots of people get rescued.

1659
01:24:54,381 --> 01:24:55,591
Oh?

1660
01:24:55,632 --> 01:24:57,801
Oh, yeah.
My brother usually rescues me.

1661
01:24:57,843 --> 01:24:59,428
If he can keep off the tail
for more than 20 minutes.

1662
01:24:59,469 --> 01:25:01,304
-[scoffs]
-Oh.

1663
01:25:01,346 --> 01:25:05,017
Randy little bugger. Up and down
like the Assyrian Empire.
[laughs]

1664
01:25:05,059 --> 01:25:07,185
[music resumes]

1665
01:25:09,980 --> 01:25:12,441
Hello. Your family arrived then?

1666
01:25:12,482 --> 01:25:13,316
